<p><img src="http://community.dur.ac.uk/butler.jcr/application/views/involved/img/upload/067.jpg" alt="" /></p><h1>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; JBRFc</h1><p>Despite being a young club, JBRFC has had much success since it's inception in 2006 having achieved the Premiership and Cup double in an unbeaten 08-09 season.&nbsp;</p><p>The club currently sits in the 2nd division of the inter college league and are looking to chase promotion to the top division in 2014/15&nbsp;after winning our last five league games of last season.</p><p>If&nbsp;you'd like to get involved then come along and sign up with us at the Fresher's Fair, come to our taster session on Milfield Field at midday on Tuesday 30th September, or contact either myself or Dan using the email addresses below.&nbsp;</p><p>Josephine Butler also run a Women's Rugby team in conjunction with Van Mildert. For more details on taster sessions in fresher's week, or to join the club, contact Emileigh on the details below.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>President -&nbsp;James West</strong></p><p><a href="mailto:j.a.a.west@durham.ac.uk">j.a.a.west@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p><strong>Club Captain -&nbsp;Daniel Leach</strong></p><p><a href="mailto:d.g.h.leach@durham.ac.uk">d.g.h.leach@durham.ac.uk</a></p><p><strong>Women's Rugby - Emileigh Clifford</strong></p><p><strong><a href="mailto:emileigh.clifford@durham.ac.uk">emileigh.clifford@durham.ac.uk</a></strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p>